==English==
===Etymology===
First attested from [[w:1547|1547]], from [[Late Latin]] [[stupendus]] ''stunning, amazing'', from [[Latin]] [[stupere]] ''to be stunned''. See also [[stupid]].

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛndəs|-ɛndəs]]

===Noun===
#Astonishingly great or large; [[huge]];
#Of stunning volume, or degree, or excellence; [[enormous]];
====Synonyms====
*[[colossal]], [[enormous]], [[huge]], [[marvelous]], [[prodigious]], [[terrific]], [[tremendous]]
====Translations====
*Japanese: [[途轍もない]] ([[とてつもない]], totetsumonai)
*Russian: [[изумительный]]; [[громадный]]; [[огромный]]; [[грандиозный]], [[колоссальный]]